At the time of its release, it was the least expensive platform for consumer-grade wireless routers in their product lineup. :The default clock of the BCM5356U in this unit seems to be 300MHz. OEM: [[SGE]] ([http://www.twsz.com Shenzhen Gongjin Electronics Co.,Ltd.]) *[http://wiki.openwrt.org/toh/asus/rt-n10u ''Asus RT-N10U'' on the '''OpenWrt''' Wiki] ===Overview=== *Powerful and wide coverage with 5 dBi antenna. *Bandwidth allocation and access control with 4 SSIDs. *No more dead spots at home with repeater mode. *Easy wireless printing by All-in-One printer server. ===Reviews=== * [https://www.foxnetwork.ru/index.php/component/content/article/36-reviews/92-asus-rt-n10u.html ''Asus RT-N10U'' Rewieved on '''FoxNetwork'''] (w/ low-res internal shots) :F4:6D:04 OUI ===Forum threads=== *[http://www.dd-wrt.com/phpBB2/viewtopic.php?t=152672 ''Asus RT-N10U'' on the '''DD-WRT''' forums] *[http://wl500g.info/showthread.php?t=28297&langid=3 '''wl500g.info''' thread about the device] (RU) - covers overclocking :the CPU to @500MHz and upgrading the [http://wl500g.info/showthread.php?28297-Asus-RT-N10U-N10UB-%F1-%EF%F0%EE%F8%E8%E2%EA%EE%E9-%EE%F2-%FD%ED%F2%F3%E7%E8%E0%F1%F2%EE%E2&p=246107#post246107 RAM to 64MB]
